The paper proposes a space-efficient implementation of a dynamic keyword dictionary, which involves data structures and algorithms for storing and retrieving strings. This topic is closely related to several sub-fields of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), databases (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Given the focus on data structures and algorithms, cs.DS is the most likely sub-category. However, the paper also discusses experiments on real-world datasets, which suggests a connection to cs.IR and cs.DB. The use of compact hash trie representations and path decomposition techniques may also be relevant to cs.AI and cs.LG, which deal with efficient data processing and machine learning algorithms.
